<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" Description="">
  <CalDefFileVersion>13</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>29SEP14</Date>
    <Description>Added Usage on HIGH</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>4/21/2015</Date>
    <Description>Per request from Thiep Nguyen updated the ECO_ROUTE_CURVE and DEFAULT_POI_FUEL_STATION cals to include MID usage for MY18 since MY18 is the first use case where a MID CSM with NAV could be used. Also, updated the description shown in the Cal database for both the ECO_ROUTE_CURVE and DEFAULT_POI_FUEL_STATION Cals to clarify the ENABLE_APPICATION_NAVIGATION calibration within the Global_Info.caldef is used as the condition criteria for enabling the ECO_ROUTE_CURVE and DEFAULT_POI_FUEL_STATION Cals. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>8/13/2015</Date>
    <Description>Updated the CAL default value used for the ECO_ROUTE_CURVE CAL within this CalDef due to the update within the NavApp.enumdef file to make the enumeration names more generic for this CAL.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>2/3/2016</Date>
    <Description>Added new CAL, called PAY_BROADCAST_TRAFFIC, in this caldef file.</Description>
    <Author>Thiep Nguyen</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>12/18/2017</Date>
    <Description>For RTC CR#: 1659638 added a new calibration called MODULE_ORIENTATION within the NavApp.caldef.</Description>
    <Author>Thiep Nguyen</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>4/11/2018</Date>
    <Description>Made the following updates within the NavApp.caldef: Per CR# 949588, added one new calibration called K_STREETVIEW_DATA_ENABLE.  Per CR# 949991, added one new calibration called K_PREDICTIVE_CARDS_ENABLE.  Per CR# 992975, added four new calibrations: 1) K_DESTINATION_HIGHLIGHT_ENABLE 2) K_DESTINATION_HIGHLIGHT_PIN_HEIGHT_FROM_GROUND 3) K_DESTINATION_VIEW_ANGLE_HORIZONTAL 4) K_DESTINATION_VIEW_ANGLE_VERTICAL.  Per CR# 993467, added five new calibrations: 1) K_DYNAMIC_ARROW_ON_PATH_OVERLAY_ENABLE 2) K_WALL_ARROW_HEIGHT_FROM_GROUND 3) K_WALL_ARROW_OVERLAY_ENABLE 4) K_WALL_ARROW_START_DISTANCE_BEFORE_MANEUVER 5) K_WALL_ARROW_START_TIME_BEFORE_MANEUVER.   Per CR# 1346230, added one new calibration called K_RANGE_PROJECTION_AND_SMART_ROUTING_TYPE.  Per CR# 1350273, added one new calibration called K_CROWD_SENSE_DATA_NAVIGATION_ENABLE.  For CR1777673, 1) K_LANE_GUIDANCE_HEIGHT_FROM_GROUND 2) K_POI_CARD_HEIGHT_FROM_GROUND. </Description>
    <Author>Paul Wagner</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>May 8 2019</Date>
    <Description>CR: 2227402 add 2 new calibration: K_AR_LANE_GUIDANCE_ENABLE and K_AR_PARKING_CARDS_ENABLE</Description>
    <Author>Chalan Munasinghe/Evelyn Job</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>05/23/2019</Date>
    <Description>Per CR# 2096904 Added Cal HD_MAP_AND_ROUTE_TYPE</Description>
    <Author>Chalan Munasinghe</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>05-28-2019</Date>
    <Description>Dave/Chalan/Ginnard: Per CR#2096904 added a clarification note for the following 4 calibrations that these calibrations does not apply for GAS: 1)ECO_ROUTE_CURVE 2)PAY_BROADCAST_TRAFFIC 3)K_PREDICTIVE_CARDS_ENABLE 4)K_STREETVIEW_DATA_ENABLE; Removed &quot;K_CROWD_SENSE_DATA_NAVIGATION_ENABLE&quot; based on rejected CR#1350273</Description>
    <Author>Chalan Munasinghe</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>04/07/2020</Date>
    <Description>For CR#2363628 Added the following Cals: (1) EV_ENERGY_MODEL_FEATURE_MAP and (2) EV_ENERGY_MODEL_PARAMETERS.</Description>
    <Author>Chalan Munasinghe</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="This calibration sets all the parametric EV vehicle data for the Navigation Vehicle Energy Model calculation that will determine the energy along the route and charging spot recommendations.  It basically is used to calculate the range of the vehicle.  This Calibration is actually a Blob that is composed of many individual parameters.  The Blob composition will be further broken down in the functional requirements section.  The software development team responsible for EV will need to create the Blob cal creation tools necessary." Name="EV_ENERGY_MODEL_PARAMETERS" References="MY23 Nav Partner App FNC" Usage="MID,HIGH,VCU,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_sSDTUHkEEeqxUKJdn1c1Ew</CalID>
    <Type>BinaryFile</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>04-07-2020</Date>
      <Description>Initial Release of this Calibration</Description>
      <Author>Chalan Munasinghe</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <BinaryFile>
      <Filename>sample_blob_512kb</Filename>
      <Data></Data>
      <Length>524000</Length>
      <Checksum>3612676257</Checksum>
    </BinaryFile>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="This EV calibration parameter includes a set of Boolean parameters that is configurable to individually Enables/Disables the sending of this data to the VEM Model. If the value is set to &quot;0&quot;: the Nav System will not send the data to the VEM. If the value is set to &quot;1&quot;: the Nav System will send the data to the VEM." Name="EV_ENERGY_MODEL_FEATURE_MAP" Usage="MID,HIGH,VCU,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_oR8l0HkCEeqxUKJdn1c1Ew</CalID>
    <Type>EnumIntegerMap</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
