  <CalDefinition Description="The use case of this calibration is intended to display Super Cruise/Ultra Cruise map and route where applicable. This calibration shall be set to the following: &quot;0=None when SuperCruise or UltraCruise is not applicable&quot;, &#x201c;1=SuperCruise  for RPO: UKL&#x201d;,  and &quot;2=UltraCruise for RPO: UKR&quot;" Name="HD_MAP_AND_ROUTE_TYPE" References="Automotive Service Solution Function (Reference Module in DNG)" Usage="MID,HIGH,VCU,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_lubiQACHEeqcM4o___siSA</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>03-21-2019</Date>
      <Description>Initial Release of this Cal</Description>
      <Author>Chalan Munasinghe</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Enumeration>
      <EnumID>_lVU7MACGEeqcM4o___siSA</EnumID>
      <Value>0</Value>
    </Enumeration>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Default Fuel type POI search base on vehicle configuration. Also note the condition criteria for this calibration being enabled is the ENABLE_APPLICATION_NAVIGATION in the Global_Info3.caldef file within the Cal database. When, the ENABLE_APPLICATION_NAVIGATION calibration is set to true this calibration is enable else it is not. [ Old MY20 NAV ] " Name="DEFAULT_POI_FUEL_STATION" References="GIS-504 Navigation UI Specification - Form and Behavior, GIS-620 Navigation Functional Requirements" Usage="MID,HIGH,VCU,GLOBALA,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_3GQ9gMZaEeO9-d-JqUwEvQ</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>4/17/14</Date>
      <Description>The POI shall have the information to  indicate fuel types supported at the station.</Description>
      <Author>GIS-620-028</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>4/20/2015</Date>
      <Description>Per request from Thiep Nguyen updated this Cal to include MID CSM usage for MY18 since MY18 is the first use case where a MID CSM with NAV could be used. And, updated description for this Cal to clarify the ENABLE_APPICATION_NAVIGATION calibration within the Global_Info.caldef is used as the condition criteria for enabling the DEFAULT_POI_FUEL_STATION calibration.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Enumeration>
      <EnumID>_r2OaQMV2EeOEJ-R0VVyC2A</EnumID>
      <Value>0</Value>
    </Enumeration>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Calibration represents the curves that define ECO routing performance and criteria base vehicle specific. Also, note the condition criteria for this calibration being enabled is the ENABLE_APPLICATION_NAVIGATION. Also, note the condition criteria for this calibration being enabled is the ENABLE_APPLICATION_NAVIGATION within the Global_Info3.caldef file in the Cal database. When, the ENABLE_APPLICATION_NAVIGATION calibration is set to true this calibration is enable else it is not.  [ Old MY20 NAV ]; THIS CALIBRATION SHOULD NOT BE USED FOR APPLICATIONS USING GAS" Name="ECO_ROUTE_CURVE" References="GIS-504 Navigation UI Specification - Form and Behavior, GIS-620 Navigation Functional Requirements" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_XeJ64MTnEeOePMFnmOVt0g</CalID>
