  <CalDefinition Description="The AR System utilizes the K_DYNAMIC_ARROW_ON_PATH_ENABLE calibratable Configuration parameter to disable or enable the the AR &quot;Dynamic Arrow on Path&quot; functionality.  This feature can be turned off by this calibration if it is not functional at the time of vehicle production.  This feature can also be turned off for non-Info3.5C vehicles that do not support Augmented Reality.  [ New MY21 AR ]" Name="K_DYNAMIC_ARROW_ON_PATH_OVERLAY_ENABLE" References="GIS-620 Navigation Functional Requirements, GIS-1064 Augmented Reality UI Specification - Form and Behavior" Usage="MID,HIGH,VCU,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_w9L6QDqDEeesh_Gsoan6Vg</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>4/11/2018</Date>
      <Description>CR 993467 MFL D20-66_21MY: Cadillac AR Navigation - upcoming maneuvers - for Info 3.5C only, initial release of K_DYNAMIC_ARROW_ON_PATH_OVERLAY_ENABLE for GIS-620</Description>
      <Author>Paul Wagner</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>true</Value>
